{0 Find references (backlinks)}

Find all locations in the vault that link {e to} a given file or
heading — the inverse of go-to-definition.

{1 Input}

A cursor position (0-based line and character) in a markdown file that
belongs to a vault with a built index.

{1 Activation}

The request is [textDocument/references].  The server advertises
[referencesProvider] in its capabilities.

Two activation modes:

{ol
  {- {b Cursor on a link}: find all other references to the same
     resolved target.}
  {- {b Cursor on a heading or block ID}: find all links that target
     this specific heading/block in this file.}
}

If the cursor is not on a link, heading, or block ID, no results are
returned.

{1 Collection}

{2 Step 1 — Determine the reference target}

{ul
  {- If the cursor is on a link, resolve it via
     {!Oystermark.Vault.Resolve.resolve} to obtain the target path
     (and optional fragment).}
  {- If the cursor is on a heading, the target is (current file,
     heading slug).}
  {- If the cursor is on a block ID, the target is (current file,
     block ID).}
}

{2 Step 2 — Scan the vault}

Walk every indexed document and collect links whose resolution matches
the reference target:

{ul
  {- {b Path-only target}: collect links that resolve to the same
     file, regardless of fragment.}
  {- {b Path + fragment target}: collect links that resolve to the
     same file {e and} whose fragment matches.}
}

{1 Result}

A list of LSP [Location] objects, one per referring link.  Each
location covers the full byte range of the link syntax (brackets
included).

{t
  | Field | Value                              |
  |-------|------------------------------------|
  | uri   | file URI of the referring document |
  | range | byte range of the link             |
}

Results are sorted by (uri, range.start) for determinism.

{1 Edge cases}

{ul
  {- {b Unresolved link under cursor}: no results (cannot determine
     target).}
  {- {b No references found}: empty list.}
  {- {b Self-references}: a document linking to itself is included
     in results.}
  {- {b Embed links} ([![[note]]]): included as references, same as
     regular wikilinks.}
}

{1 Assumptions and limitations}

{ul
  {- Scanning all indexed documents on every request.  For large
     vaults, a pre-built reverse index may be needed.}
  {- Only links in the vault index are considered; files outside the
     vault root are not scanned.}
}
